Dave,

(This may belong to the wish-list)

Is is possible to reduce an appearance of negative preexponential 
factors to a level of warning (unless you use it in a log, of course).

I understand that kT/h*exp(dS/T) can't result in a negative value, 
but we do encounter it occasionally. An example is one of the NH2+NO 
channels (see Miller, Glarborg, Springer Ser. Chem. Phys. 61, 318, 
1996; appears in Glarborg 98 model). One could certainly refit the 
rate coefficient expression in question...

Sincerely,
           Zoran
